 defendants allows plaintiffs to tie up defendants in complex and costly legal processes. The book also examines the dangers SLAPPs pose to political expression and to the quality and integrity of our democratic political institutions. Finally, the book examines the need to regulate SLAPPs in Canada and assesses various regulatory proposals. In Canada, considerable attention has been paid to the “legalization of politics” and the impact on the Charter in diverting political activism into the judicial arena. SLAPPs, however, are an under-studied element of this process, and in their obstruction of political engagement through recourse to the courts they have profound implications for democratic practice.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aFrivolous suits (Civil procedure)zCanada. 0aPolitical activistsxLegal status, laws, etcxCanada. 0aPolitical participationxCanada. 0aPolitical participationzCanada. 0aPolitical questions and judicial powerxCanada. 4aLaw. 4aPolitical Science. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Censorship.2bisacsh  aBlack Lives Matter.  acapitalism.  acollective activism.  acollective politics.  adefamation laws.  afreedom of assembly.  afreedom of speech.  alaws against dissent.  aneoliberalism.  apolitical activism.  apolitical debate.  apolitical dissent.  apolitical lobbying.  apolitical organizing.  aprotection for dissent.  aresistance to corporate culture.  aslapp.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2014z978311127407208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2014z978311127709740uhttps://doi.org/10.51644/978155458930240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781554589302423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781554589302/original  a978-3-11-127407-2  ACUP Complete e